Quantum Computing Algorithm Engine Concepts
|
├── Quantum Hardware Abstraction
|   ├── Qubits
|   │   ├── Superposition
|   │   └── Entanglement
|   ├── Quantum Gates
|   │   ├── Single-Qubit Gates (X, Y, Z, H, T)
|   │   └── Multi-Qubit Gates (CNOT, Toffoli, SWAP)
|   └── Quantum Circuits
|
├── Quantum Algorithmic Primitives
|   ├── Quantum Fourier Transform (QFT)
|   ├── Phase Estimation
|   ├── Amplitude Amplification
|   └── Measurement and Readout
|
├── Core Quantum Algorithms
|   ├── Shor’s Algorithm (Factoring)
|   ├── Grover’s Algorithm (Unstructured Search)
|   ├── Variational Algorithms
|   │   ├── VQE (Variational Quantum Eigensolver)
|   │   └── QAOA (Quantum Approximate Optimization Algorithm)
|   └── Quantum Simulation Algorithms
|       ├── Trotterization
|       └── Hamiltonian Simulation
|
├── Domain-Specific Adaptation Layers
|   ├── Materials Science (e.g., Electronic Structure)
|   ├── Cryptography (e.g., RSA Cracking)
|   ├── Climate Modeling (e.g., Quantum Annealing)
|   ├── Genomics (e.g., Optimization Problems)
|   └── Particle Physics (e.g., Lattice QCD Simulation)
|
├── Quantum-Classical Hybrid Orchestration
|   ├── Classical Optimizers (e.g., COBYLA, SPSA)
|   ├── Hybrid Workflows (e.g., VQE Loop)
|   └── Middleware (e.g., Qiskit Runtime, Cirq Engine)
|
└── Benchmarking and Optimization
    ├── Fidelity and Noise Analysis
    ├── Quantum Volume and Depth Metrics
    ├── Classical Baseline Comparison
    └── Quantum Advantage Characterization
